<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="82" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="82">
Turkey. 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" rank="kingdom">Plantae</taxonomicName>
Lyciae, ad fonts reginis 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alpinae">alpinae</taxonomicName>
montis Elmalu, 25 Jun 1860, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">E. Bourgeau 271</emphasis>
(lectotype, 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">here designated</emphasis>
: G [G00330280 image!]; isolectotypes: G [G00380172 image!, p.p. central and right top two samples], G [G0038173 image!], K [K-000789856 image!]).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="82" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Armenia, Azerbaijan, Afghanistan, Georgia, Iran, Kyrgyz Republic, Pakistan, Turkey and Turkmenistan(?).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="82" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="82">
This taxon, accepted as 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Eremopoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eremopoa bellula" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bellula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Eremopoa bellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by several authors (see Names of Uncertain Application below), was first recognised infraspecifically by 
<bibRefCitation author="Boissier, PE" editor="Boissier, PE" journalOrPublisher="5. H. Georg, Basilae" pageId="20" pageNumber="89" pagination="432 - 692" refId="B3" refString="Boissier, PE, 1884. Ordo CXLI. Gramineae. In: Boissier, PE, Ed., Flora Orientalis, vol. 5. H. Georg, Basilae: 432 - 692" title="Ordo CXLI. Gramineae." volumeTitle="Flora Orientalis, vol." year="1884">Boissier (1884)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boiss" authorityYear="1884" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa persica var. alpina" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="persica" variety="alpina">Poa persica var. alpina</taxonomicName>
. The variety is common in the highest elevations at which the genus occurs, in the alpine of Turkey, Iran and Afghanistan to the Pamir mountains, reaching 4000 m. Further study is needed to clarify the distinction of var. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boiss" authorityYear="1884" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="var. alpina" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="persica" variety="alpina">alpina</taxonomicName>
from var. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Asch &amp; Graebn" authorityYear="1900" baseAuthorityName="Trin." class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="var. diaphora" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="persica" variety="diaphora">diaphora</taxonomicName>
and these from 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Eremopoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eremopoa bellula" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bellula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Eremopoa bellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as the material placed here appears heterogenous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="82">
Of the six syntypes of var. 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Eremopoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="var. alpina" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="bellula" variety="alpina">alpina</taxonomicName>
cited by Boissier (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Bourgeau 271</emphasis>
, hab. in alpinis, montes supra Elmali Lyciae [G00380172, G0038173, G00330280, K000789856]; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Kotschy 12</emphasis>
, Tarus Cilicicus, 5
<normalizedToken originalValue="–6000’">-6000'</normalizedToken>
; Prairies humides de la region alpine du Taurus, au Boulgarmden [as 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">12d</emphasis>
: G00330281, K000789851 image!]; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Balansa s.n.</emphasis>
, Jul-Aug 1855 [K000789857, P02358251 p.p. bottom right]; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Blanche s.n</emphasis>
., Libani cacuminal; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Kotschy 477</emphasis>
, mons Kuh Delu Persiae australis, 10 Jun 1842 [BM000959359 image!, E!, G00308632 image!, P02358251! p.p. &quot;fo. pygmaea&quot; bottom left]), we select 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Bourgeau 271</emphasis>
as the lectotype as it is typical of the form. As noted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Samuelsson, G" journalOrPublisher="Iranian Journal of Botany" pageId="22" pageNumber="91" refId="B47" refString="Samuelsson, G, 1950. In: Rechinger KH (Ed.) Zur Flora von Cypren (Reliquiae Samuelssonianae II.). Arkiv foer Botanik, n.s.1(9): 417." title="In: Rechinger KH (Ed.) Zur Flora von Cypren (Reliquiae Samuelssonianae II.). Arkiv foer Botanik, n. s. 1 (9): 417." year="1950">Samuelsson (1950)</bibRefCitation>
, the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Sintenis</emphasis>
syntype (mons Troodos, Cypri) represents a separate form that is treated here as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Lindb., Arsbok-Vuosik. Soc. Sci. Fenn. 20 B (7): 5. 1942 (emend. Lindberg" authorityYear="1946" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa sintenisii" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sintenisii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Poa sintenisii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa persica" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Poa persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
var. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“minor”">
&quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">minor</emphasis>
&quot;
</normalizedToken>
Boiss. (cited by Mill, in Fl. Turkey 9: 492. 1985) is a nomen nudum since it is a herbarium name on 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Bourgeau 271</emphasis>
, syntype of var. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boiss" authorityYear="1884" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="var. alpina" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="persica" variety="alpina">alpina</taxonomicName>
Boiss.; this name is also inscribed on 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="82">Kotschy 12d</emphasis>
(p.p. G00308174), but the latter is original material, not a syntype, mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Boissier, PE" editor="Boissier, PE" journalOrPublisher="5. H. Georg, Basilae" pageId="20" pageNumber="89" pagination="432 - 692" refId="B3" refString="Boissier, PE, 1884. Ordo CXLI. Gramineae. In: Boissier, PE, Ed., Flora Orientalis, vol. 5. H. Georg, Basilae: 432 - 692" title="Ordo CXLI. Gramineae." volumeTitle="Flora Orientalis, vol." year="1884">Boissier (1884)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
